medieval women home medieval women faith love and learning is an umbrella title for three separate but interlocking elements an undergraduate lecture course a graduate colloquium and a speaker series that links them the speaker series held during the undergraduate lecture course brings together five of the most influential and exciting scholars in the field of medieval women's studies and is open to the public as well as playing a central role in both the undergraduate and graduate course all three speaker series undergraduate lecture and graduate colloquium are dedicated to exploring the major roles that women played in responding to and indeed shaping medieval culture and society
